description:
In 2018, This is how much money you needed in Venezuela to Buy 1 roll of toilet paper 
The amount was 2.6m Bolivars, equivalent to $0.40 cent

It highlights the issue of hyperinflation, when money literally becomes worthless.

It does make you think though, why buy toilet paper when you can just use the money?
